com.phunware.advertising

Class PwVideoInterstitialAd

  • java.lang.Object
    • VideoInterstitialAdImpl
      • com.phunware.advertising.PwVideoInterstitialAd

  • public class PwVideoInterstitialAd
extends VideoInterstitialAdImpl
    Video interstitials are full screen ads that display a video ad in their own Activity. Video interstitials are best used at discrete stopping points in your app's flow, such as at the end of a game level, or when the player dies.

    Simple example:

     PwVideoInterstitialAd videoInterstitialAd = PwVideoInterstitialAd.getInstance(context, zoneId);
 videoInterstitialAd.show(); // video interstitial is loaded and shown asynchronously
    Instances of PwVideoInterstitialAd are not safe for use by multiple threads.

      • load

        public void load()
        Fire off an asynchronous request to the server for an ad. Use isLoaded() or PwVideoInterstitialAd.PwVideoInterstitialAdListener to determine when an ad is loaded.

      • show

        public void show()
        Display interstitial to user. If an ad is not loaded, load() will be called and the ad will be loaded and shown asynchronously. Use isLoaded() or PwVideoInterstitialAd.PwVideoInterstitialAdListener to determine when an ad is loaded.
